==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*arƀējiðiz'' ‘hardship’, from a verb ''*arƀējō'' ‘be orphaned’.  Cognate with Old Saxon [[arƀed]] (Dutch [[arbeid]], Swedish [[arbete]]), Old High German [[arbeit]] (German [[Arbeit]]), Old Norse [[erfiði]], Gothic [[𐌰𐍂𐌱𐌰𐌹𐌸𐍃]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'æarveðe/

===Noun===
'''earfeþe''' ''n''
# [[hardship]], [[suffering]]; [[labour]]

